Bootstrap: docker
From: pytorch/pytorch:2.5.1-cuda12.1-cudnn9-runtime

%post
    apt-get update -y && \
    apt-get install -y git libgl1 libglib2.0-0 && \
    apt-get clean && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    mkdir -p /data/BCI-asp /data/MIST-HER2

    pip install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip

    # Model-specific packages (beyond PyTorch base).
    # visdom is NOT installed -- it is never used when --display_id -1 is passed,
    # and visdom 0.2.4 fails to build on Python 3.11 (broken pkg_resources dependency).
    pip install --no-cache-dir \
        "dominate==2.9.1" \
        "GPUtil==1.4.0" \
        "opencv-python-headless==4.10.0.84" \
        "packaging==24.2" \
        "scipy==1.13.1"

%labels
    Author vsc21212
    Model ASP
    BaseImage pytorch/pytorch:2.5.1-cuda12.1-cudnn9-runtime
    PyTorch 2.5.1+cu121
    Python 3.11
    Benchmark InViLabVirtualStainingBenchmark

%help
    ASP (Adaptive Supervised PatchNCE) container for the InViLab virtual staining benchmark.
    Python 3.11, PyTorch 2.5.1 (cu121), CUDA 12.1 runtime.
    The cluster CUDA 12.x driver is backward compatible with this runtime.

    ASP uses --dataset_mode aligned with separate trainA/trainB folders
    (not side-by-side AB images). BCI requires a BCI-asp.sqsh whose top level
    contains trainA/, trainB/, testA/, testB/. MIST-HER2.sqsh is used directly
    (its top level is already trainA/, trainB/, valA/, valB/).

    Always pass --display_id -1 to suppress visdom. Never omit this flag on the cluster.

    Training (BCI example):
      apptainer exec --nv \
        -B $VSC_DATA:$VSC_DATA \
        -B $VSC_SCRATCH/BCI-asp.sqsh:$VSC_SCRATCH/sqsh_mnt/BCI-asp:image-src=/ \
        $VSC_SCRATCH/containers/asp_nvidia.sif \
        python $VSC_DATA/projects/asp/code/AdaptiveSupervisedPatchNCE/train.py \
          --dataroot $VSC_SCRATCH/sqsh_mnt/BCI-asp \
          --model cpt --CUT_mode FastCUT ...

    Inference (BCI example):
      apptainer exec --nv \
        -B $VSC_DATA:$VSC_DATA \
        -B $VSC_SCRATCH/BCI-asp.sqsh:$VSC_SCRATCH/sqsh_mnt/BCI-asp:image-src=/ \
        $VSC_SCRATCH/containers/asp_nvidia.sif \
        python $VSC_DATA/projects/asp/code/AdaptiveSupervisedPatchNCE/test.py \
          --dataroot $VSC_SCRATCH/sqsh_mnt/BCI-asp \
          --phase test --preprocess none ...
